 <fr:p>We must check that for every <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b:B]]></fr:tex>, the <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001Q.xml"
addr="erct-001Q"
title="Fiber">fiber</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> at <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001I.xml"
addr="erct-001I"
title="Proposition">proposition</fr:link>. Fixing <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[u_0,u_1:\mathsf {fiber}\,f\,b]]></fr:tex> we must check that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[u_0=u_1]]></fr:tex>. We let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[  \mathopen {}\left \lparen a_0,p_0\right \rparen \mathclose {} \equiv  u_0]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[  \mathopen {}\left \lparen a_1,p_1\right \rparen \mathclose {} \equiv  u_1]]></fr:tex> so that we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p_0\colon  fa_0=b]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p_1\colon  fa_1=b]]></fr:tex>. Invoking the <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-0010.xml"
addr="erct-0010"
title="Path object">path object</fr:link> structure on <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001Q.xml"
addr="erct-001Q"
title="Fiber">fibers</fr:link> (<fr:ref
addr="erct-001R"
href="erct-001R.xml"
taxon="Example" />), it suffices to exhibit the following data:</fr:p>
 <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[   \begin {aligned}    \phi &\colon  a_0 = a_1\\    \psi &\colon  p_0 = \mathsf {act}_{f}\phi \cdot  p_1   \end {aligned}  ]]></fr:tex>

  <fr:p>As <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is an <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001K.xml"
addr="erct-001K"
title="Contractible types are propositions">embedding</fr:link>, the map <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {act}_{f}\colon  a_0 = a_1 \to  fa_0 = fa_1]]></fr:tex> has an <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-000W.xml"
addr="erct-000W"
title="Inverse">inverse</fr:link> 
 <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left \lparen \mathsf {act}_{f}^{-1},\epsilon ,\eta ,\chi \right \rparen \mathclose {}]]></fr:tex>
.</fr:p>

 <fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha  \colon  fa_0 = fa_1]]></fr:tex> be the concatenation <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p_0\cdot  p_1^{-1}]]></fr:tex>. Therefore we may define:</fr:p>

 <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[   \begin {aligned}    \phi &\colon  a_0 = a_1\\    \phi &:\equiv  \mathsf {act}_{f}^{-1} \alpha    \end {aligned}  ]]></fr:tex>

 <fr:p>To define <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\psi  \colon  p_0=\mathsf {act}_{f}\phi \cdot  p_1]]></fr:tex> we use the counit of our <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-000W.xml"
addr="erct-000W"
title="Inverse">inverse</fr:link> as we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon  \alpha  \colon  \mathsf {act}_{f}\phi  = p_0\cdot  p_1^{-1}]]></fr:tex>. Thus concatenating on either side with <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p_1]]></fr:tex> we have our goal, modulo the laws of identification concatenation and symmetry respectively.</fr:p>
